    helpText: 'Regular physical activity is crucial for recovery as it naturally releases endorphins, reduces anxiety and depression, improves sleep quality, and provides healthy coping mechanisms for stress and cravings. Plan specific types of exercise for each day of the week such as walking, strength training, yoga, or swimming, starting with realistic goals based on your current fitness level and gradually increasing intensity as your body heals. This structured approach to fitness creates routine, improves physical health damaged by substance use, and provides a powerful tool for managing difficult emotions without turning to substances.'
