<parameter name="old_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-43',
    prompt: 'Establish a comprehensive sleep hygiene routine and track your sleep patterns for two weeks to support recovery healing',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Quality sleep is essential for brain healing and emotional regulation during recovery, as addiction often severely disrupts natural sleep cycles and poor sleep increases relapse risk. Create a specific bedtime routine including consistent sleep and wake times, removing screens 1 hour before bed, keeping your bedroom cool and dark, and avoiding caffeine after 2 PM, then track your sleep quality and hours each night for 14 days. This structured approach to sleep recovery helps restore your natural circadian rhythms, improves mental clarity and emotional stability, and provides concrete data to identify what sleep strategies work best for your individual recovery needs.'
  }</parameter>
